WEBVTT

00:47.672 --> 00:48.840
It's that guy.

00:49.841 --> 00:51.760
What are you talking about? Which guy?

00:52.469 --> 00:54.054
Who? You mean Jun-hui?

00:54.137 --> 00:55.638
You need to explain this.

01:03.438 --> 01:04.272
Let go of her hand.

01:05.273 --> 01:06.107
Hey.

01:09.944 --> 01:11.029
Follow me.

01:16.701 --> 01:18.411
- Break it up!
- Hey!

01:18.661 --> 01:20.705
- What's the matter with you?
- My goodness.

01:20.789 --> 01:22.582
- Hey, let go!
- Jun-hui!

01:22.665 --> 01:24.501
- Hey!
- What should we do?

01:24.584 --> 01:27.045
- Follow me.
- Jun-hui, what is going on?

01:27.128 --> 01:29.589
- What is your problem?
- Be quiet.

01:29.672 --> 01:31.424
- Hey, what's going on?
- Let go.

01:31.508 --> 01:33.009
- I'm asking what's going on.
- Be quiet.

01:33.134 --> 01:35.178
- Let's talk outside.
- Damn it.

01:35.386 --> 01:37.263
Wait. Gyu-min, do you know him?

01:39.057 --> 01:41.976
- How do you know this guy?
- He's my friend.

01:42.352 --> 01:44.729
What? Your friend? My gosh.

01:45.313 --> 01:47.315
Hey, that means you're younger than me.

01:47.607 --> 01:49.609
I can't believe this.
What are you looking at?

01:51.111 --> 01:53.363
I'm telling you. I won't let this slide.

01:53.822 --> 01:56.741
What the hell is going on?
Why are you guys fighting?

01:58.952 --> 02:00.870
- Hey, what is it?
- We'll talk outside.

02:00.954 --> 02:01.830
Damn it.

02:06.126 --> 02:07.210
Did you find them?

02:07.669 --> 02:08.503
No.

02:10.004 --> 02:11.631
Where the heck did they go?

02:11.714 --> 02:13.591
They're not even outside.

02:13.967 --> 02:16.094
Hey, what is happening...

02:17.053 --> 02:19.347
I told you that I'll explain
everything later.

02:19.430 --> 02:20.974
- Why--
- That's enough.

02:21.850 --> 02:24.394
Stop that.
Go to your room and get changed first.

02:26.437 --> 02:29.566
I knew that something was up
as soon as I saw you in that dress.

02:29.858 --> 02:32.110
I was wondering
why you were acting all strange.

02:32.193 --> 02:33.111
Gosh, seriously...

02:34.445 --> 02:35.321
My goodness!

02:37.699 --> 02:38.616
Shit.

02:38.908 --> 02:39.909
Guys. Please!

02:40.785 --> 02:43.621
You guys need to at least tell me
what's going on.

02:43.913 --> 02:46.875
Why are you guys being like this?
You two are driving me nuts.

02:46.958 --> 02:48.877
Hey, I'm the one who's going nuts here.

02:49.252 --> 02:51.629
Jin-a likes him. She said it herself.

02:52.046 --> 02:53.089
What are you talking about?

02:53.339 --> 02:54.924
I just told you that he's my friend.

02:55.008 --> 02:56.926
Right, that's what baffles me even more.

02:57.719 --> 03:00.597
Hey, what is he talking about?

03:01.097 --> 03:02.807
Say something!

03:04.058 --> 03:06.019
I told you to fuck off last time,
didn't I?

03:06.769 --> 03:08.354
Are you really stalking Jin-a or what?

03:09.731 --> 03:10.732
Do you want to die?

03:10.815 --> 03:11.941
- You little...
- Hey.

03:16.070 --> 03:19.198
What did you say?
Did you call him a stalker?

03:23.161 --> 03:24.579
He two-timed Jin-a.

03:25.830 --> 03:27.373
That's why she ended it with him.

03:29.417 --> 03:30.877
He's a real piece of shit.

03:34.172 --> 03:36.549
- Did you really cheat on her?
- Wait, no...

03:36.966 --> 03:38.760
Well, actually...

03:39.761 --> 03:41.971
It wasn't just me.
Jin-a also cheated on me with this guy.

03:42.055 --> 03:43.097
I told you.

03:43.348 --> 03:45.350
She told her parents that she likes him.

03:45.433 --> 03:46.517
She said that earlier.

03:50.897 --> 03:52.607
- Go.
- Seung-ho.

03:52.690 --> 03:53.650
Just go.

03:54.817 --> 03:57.612
Leave before I beat
the soul out of you myself.

03:59.155 --> 04:00.156
Are you deaf?

04:01.324 --> 04:03.243
Fuck off, you piece of shit!

04:05.620 --> 04:07.747
So you don't trust me?

04:08.623 --> 04:10.500
Fine. Have it your way.

04:10.708 --> 04:13.628
You will definitely regret it one day.

04:24.305 --> 04:26.516
Yoon Jin-a, that idiot.

04:28.226 --> 04:30.436
Hey, when did you find out?

04:30.520 --> 04:32.480
You should have told me
when you found out!

04:34.148 --> 04:36.567
You talk as if you've always been
interested in her life.

04:38.069 --> 04:39.070
Gosh.

04:40.780 --> 04:42.407
I should have kicked his ass.

04:45.576 --> 04:46.953
I told you to stay out of it.

04:47.954 --> 04:49.747
Didn’t you see what was going on?

04:50.456 --> 04:52.750
Gosh, you're so slow.

04:52.959 --> 04:54.919
He said my sister has feelings for you.

04:55.003 --> 04:56.587
How could I think straight?

04:59.215 --> 05:00.550
Gosh.

05:18.109 --> 05:21.112
What happened? Did you guys fight?

05:22.155 --> 05:23.489
Gyu-min cheated on her.

05:25.325 --> 05:26.159
And?

05:26.868 --> 05:29.287
Before that, Jun-hui, why did you--

05:29.370 --> 05:30.204
Mom.

05:32.665 --> 05:34.292
Gyu-min kept showing up and bothering me.

05:35.084 --> 05:36.961
So I asked Jun-hui
to pretend to be my boyfriend

05:37.045 --> 05:38.337
to shake him off.

05:38.421 --> 05:41.215
- What you said about having feelings for--
- I didn't mean it.

05:41.299 --> 05:43.217
I had to say it to make him go away.

05:43.843 --> 05:45.053
Do I have to explain myself?

05:45.428 --> 05:47.847
Well, I just couldn't believe
what I heard.

05:47.930 --> 05:49.140
Do you know how shocked I was?

05:49.223 --> 05:51.601
That's enough. Don't scold her.

05:51.809 --> 05:53.686
She's not the one to blame.

05:55.188 --> 05:57.315
Anyway, thank you, Jun-hui.

05:58.149 --> 06:00.651
Not at all. I'm sorry for causing a scene.

06:01.235 --> 06:03.362
You shouldn't apologize for that.

06:03.946 --> 06:05.615
We are the ones
who should apologize to you.

06:06.324 --> 06:08.117
This is embarrassing, Jin-a.

06:09.035 --> 06:11.287
Aren't you old enough
to stay away from two-timers?

06:12.205 --> 06:14.791
- You shouldn't date anyone again.
- Be quiet.

06:15.166 --> 06:17.126
- You two should eat.
- It's all right.

06:17.668 --> 06:20.004
I'll come back at another time.

06:49.325 --> 06:50.326
Come here.

06:51.285 --> 06:52.370
Tell me the truth.

06:52.995 --> 06:54.372
What happened with Gyu-min is true.

06:54.622 --> 06:56.332
But what you said
about Jun-hui isn't, right?

06:56.707 --> 06:58.709
- Mom, please.
- Goodness.

06:59.210 --> 07:00.795
Aren't you embarrassed to see Jun-hui?

07:00.878 --> 07:04.006
He's your brother's friend.
What would he think of you?

07:04.215 --> 07:07.677
He's going to think that you're a mess
who can't get the relationship working.

07:07.969 --> 07:09.137
And what about Seung-ho?

07:09.220 --> 07:11.973
He must be ashamed
to have his friend involved.

07:12.390 --> 07:15.810
What is wrong with you
that you always end up with losers?

07:15.893 --> 07:18.521
Why would you do something
I didn't ask for?

07:18.604 --> 07:20.189
Why did you invite Gyu-min over?

07:20.523 --> 07:22.442
You're too eager to marry me off
to any guy.

07:22.733 --> 07:24.569
Do you think marriage is a joke?

07:24.652 --> 07:25.945
How dare you raise your voice?

07:27.905 --> 07:28.739
Think about it.

07:28.990 --> 07:32.076
If you were good to him,
Gyu-min wouldn't have cheated on you.

07:32.160 --> 07:33.578
I've told you countless times.

07:33.744 --> 07:34.662
Mom!

07:34.996 --> 07:35.872
My goodness.

07:36.414 --> 07:38.040
You are the only one who is still single.

07:38.124 --> 07:40.251
Everyone else's daughters had no problem

07:40.334 --> 07:42.795
getting married and settling down
when they were supposed to.

07:42.879 --> 07:46.424
What's your problem?
Why aren't you settled at this age?

07:46.507 --> 07:48.509
The problem is that I am not like them.

07:48.593 --> 07:50.303
Maybe their mothers are nicer than mine.

07:50.511 --> 07:52.638
Why you little...

07:53.347 --> 07:54.640
Don't.

08:25.171 --> 08:27.840
I came to steal your beer.
I guess I got caught in the act.

08:32.970 --> 08:34.180
You look upset.

08:34.931 --> 08:36.015
Did you get into a fight?

08:37.016 --> 08:38.142
I'm a bit tired.

08:38.476 --> 08:39.477
You did.

08:40.102 --> 08:42.480
I'm glad you didn't get beat up.

08:43.022 --> 08:44.190
Did you kick the other's butt?

08:45.525 --> 08:46.734
I'm going to wash up.

08:47.276 --> 08:48.277
Would you like some beer?

08:48.945 --> 08:49.820
No thanks.

08:51.239 --> 08:52.823
I guess he really got into a fight.

08:54.450 --> 08:55.701
Whether she gets married

08:56.619 --> 08:59.205
or dies as an old hag, I don't care.

09:00.164 --> 09:01.916
I wasn't talking nonsense.

09:02.250 --> 09:04.043
I nagged her
because I was worried about her.

09:04.126 --> 09:06.546
- Why can't she understand--
- Go to sleep.

09:06.754 --> 09:09.257
I can't go to sleep.
I'm boiling with anger.

09:10.383 --> 09:12.635
Things are harder for Jin-a.

09:14.470 --> 09:17.181
You didn't do your part properly either.

09:17.932 --> 09:20.142
You were never the tenacious type.

09:20.226 --> 09:22.770
That's why you never got the chance
to become an executive.

09:25.356 --> 09:27.942
Why would you bring that up now?

09:28.025 --> 09:29.026
Why wouldn't I?

09:29.110 --> 09:31.821
If you kept your place
in the company without retiring,

09:31.904 --> 09:33.698
Jin-a wouldn't have gone through this.

09:34.073 --> 09:36.492
This happened
because he looked down on us.

09:56.762 --> 09:57.763
I'm sorry.

10:00.016 --> 10:01.434
There's no need to be sorry.

10:03.352 --> 10:05.271
You didn't fight him, did you?

10:06.772 --> 10:08.065
He tried to hit Jun-hui.

10:08.149 --> 10:09.191
He hit him?

10:09.692 --> 10:11.068
I said, he tried to.

10:15.448 --> 10:17.908
You should have picked someone else
to play your boyfriend.

10:17.992 --> 10:20.161
Gyu-min went even crazier
because he's my friend.

10:21.037 --> 10:22.121
Are you dumb?

10:24.290 --> 10:27.418
Did you guys talk about anything else?

10:28.169 --> 10:31.505
Talk about what? We just told him
to fuck off before we kill him.

10:33.507 --> 10:34.550
What's wrong with you?

10:37.928 --> 10:39.805
I've been scolded enough already.

10:40.514 --> 10:41.682
Don't add on to it.

12:13.691 --> 12:14.567
Hey.

12:15.234 --> 12:16.694
What are you doing here at this hour?

12:17.987 --> 12:20.114
I came over because I sensed alcohol.

12:20.197 --> 12:22.450
- Good girl.
- Of course.

12:23.033 --> 12:24.994
- Wait, why did you...
- What?

12:25.077 --> 12:27.163
I guess you came here
because I didn't answer the door.

12:27.246 --> 12:29.165
Yes, I rang the bell,
but you weren't inside.

12:29.248 --> 12:30.666
I knew you'd be here.

12:30.749 --> 12:33.586
I came to steal some more beer. Let's go.

12:35.296 --> 12:36.297
Where's Jun-hui?

12:37.214 --> 12:40.092
He was here, but he left again soon after.

13:09.330 --> 13:12.917
I was getting tired of drinking alone.
You're my savior.

13:14.919 --> 13:17.213
Did Jun-hui go somewhere?

13:18.464 --> 13:19.507
I don't know.

13:20.633 --> 13:22.468
I think he fought with someone.

13:23.677 --> 13:25.554
He was all pouty.

13:26.514 --> 13:28.265
He wouldn't answer my questions,

13:28.349 --> 13:29.517
and he refused to drink.

13:30.351 --> 13:33.103
He may seem strong-hearted,
but he has a soft heart.

13:34.230 --> 13:37.233
I'm pretty sure
he's really angry and frustrated.

13:37.316 --> 13:39.235
That's probably why he went outside.

13:42.029 --> 13:44.615
Honestly, I feel sorry for him
every time he gets upset.

13:45.824 --> 13:47.910
He doesn't have a dad or a brother

13:47.993 --> 13:49.245
he can open up to.

13:50.412 --> 13:53.499
And it's not like he has a mom
who's always on his side.

13:53.916 --> 13:57.169
All he has is me,
but I can only do so much for him.

13:58.587 --> 14:00.923
So I try not to nag him much these days.

14:03.551 --> 14:05.302
You're not here to drink, are you?

14:06.637 --> 14:08.931
What? Why? I'm drinking. Cheers.

14:09.014 --> 14:10.558
You cannot fool me.

14:10.891 --> 14:12.518
Spill it this instance.

14:13.602 --> 14:17.106
There's nothing going on, Your Highness.

14:20.317 --> 14:21.151
Cheers.

14:23.195 --> 14:24.947
You should sleep over.

14:27.825 --> 14:30.369
- Okay.
- Do you like me that much?

14:33.289 --> 14:34.290
Of course.

15:11.160 --> 15:12.202
You're still alive.

15:18.125 --> 15:19.293
Gosh.

15:20.753 --> 15:21.587
What?

15:24.256 --> 15:26.258
I was just playing.
Why are you being so sensitive?

15:28.844 --> 15:30.888
Would you like to sample this?

15:31.680 --> 15:33.474
It's our new product.

15:37.061 --> 15:38.479
You came to work early.

15:39.021 --> 15:40.105
I came way too early.

15:43.567 --> 15:44.985
About last night...

15:46.737 --> 15:47.863
Thank you.

15:49.490 --> 15:50.491
I'm surprised.

15:51.116 --> 15:53.744
I thought you'd be mad at me
for stepping in.

15:53.827 --> 15:55.120
What?

15:55.871 --> 15:57.456
You'll be late. Go on.

16:02.336 --> 16:03.420
Hello, try this.

16:03.504 --> 16:07.132
What do you mean?
You're not making any sense.

16:07.216 --> 16:10.970
You're not answering my questions.
I feel like I'm talking to a wall.

16:25.067 --> 16:26.986
What did you mean when you said

16:27.277 --> 16:29.196
you thought I'd be mad at you?

16:31.198 --> 16:34.535
Well, because I ruined your chance
to get back together with him.

16:37.413 --> 16:39.832
Did it seem like I wanted
to get back together with him?

16:41.667 --> 16:44.753
Then why did you dress up like that
and invited him over?

16:48.090 --> 16:48.966
Fine.

16:49.633 --> 16:53.429
I guess my outfit could've made you
misunderstand the situation.

16:54.263 --> 16:58.267
- But I only did that for a reason--
- Of course, you did.

17:02.062 --> 17:03.564
I didn't invite him over.

17:04.481 --> 17:06.692
Do you think that would make sense?

17:06.775 --> 17:08.777
- Why would I invite him?
- That doesn't matter.

17:08.986 --> 17:10.404
He wouldn't have come

17:10.487 --> 17:11.905
if you had made yourself clear.

17:12.531 --> 17:13.532
That's common sense.

17:18.954 --> 17:19.997
Are we done?

17:20.581 --> 17:21.790
I'm going to go now.

17:37.848 --> 17:39.058
Gosh.

17:46.231 --> 17:47.441
Ms. Yoon, come over here.

17:54.823 --> 17:56.575
What happened to the store in Gasan?

17:56.700 --> 17:59.995
What did you do to make him send us
a notice of intent to sue?

18:00.621 --> 18:02.873
Do you know how much shit
I got from Mr. Nam?

18:03.290 --> 18:04.792
How could you mess it up so much?

18:06.794 --> 18:08.504
What in the world did you do

18:08.587 --> 18:11.298
to make an owner of a franchise store
fight against the head office?

18:13.258 --> 18:15.385
Don't just stand there. Go solve this.

18:15.511 --> 18:18.097
If you don't fix this, we'll all get fired

18:18.180 --> 18:19.890
because of you. Do you get it?

18:57.719 --> 18:59.138
- May I go in?
- Yes.

19:10.858 --> 19:12.442
You can go inside first.

19:19.032 --> 19:20.993
- Take a seat.
- Okay.

19:23.245 --> 19:24.830
- Have you been well?
- Yes.

20:13.879 --> 20:16.048
I had no other choice.

20:16.632 --> 20:19.051
The head office
should be giving us benefits.

20:19.426 --> 20:20.928
But they are all about ripping us off

20:21.011 --> 20:22.596
by forcing us to buy costly ingredients.

20:22.721 --> 20:24.723
That doesn't make sense
according to my common sense.

20:28.018 --> 20:29.144
That darn common sense.

20:33.065 --> 20:36.109
I'm sorry. I'm just so frustrated.

20:38.153 --> 20:39.404
So,

20:40.155 --> 20:42.324
since you sent us that notice,

20:42.407 --> 20:44.201
I guess you're willing
to fight until the end.

20:45.202 --> 20:47.621
Even a worm will turn sometimes.

20:47.704 --> 20:49.581
I cannot let them
take advantage of me anymore.

20:51.375 --> 20:52.417
Of course.

20:53.627 --> 20:55.545
- You shouldn't.
- Exactly.

20:58.257 --> 20:59.967
You should teach them a lesson.

21:00.300 --> 21:01.718
Fight until the very end.

21:02.052 --> 21:04.721
If this is all just pretend,
you'll gain nothing,

21:04.805 --> 21:06.890
and it'll be embarrassing. Right?

21:09.101 --> 21:11.687
You work at the head office.
I don't think you should say that.

21:13.063 --> 21:15.607
I'm going to quit soon.

21:16.566 --> 21:18.568
I can't take this anymore.

21:19.903 --> 21:22.739
I'm so sick of being a mediator

21:22.823 --> 21:25.993
between the head office
and the store owners.

21:30.872 --> 21:33.125
You might have to take it to court.

21:33.250 --> 21:35.752
I'll even testify for you
if you need me to.

21:38.171 --> 21:40.882
Are you going to quit for real?

21:40.966 --> 21:42.509
Then what are you going to do?

21:43.760 --> 21:45.220
Didn't I tell you?

21:45.804 --> 21:48.515
My dad recently retired
and is doing nothing.

21:49.141 --> 21:50.392
I'll just join him.

21:50.976 --> 21:52.477
Do you want to join too?

22:06.825 --> 22:10.954
All you did was grab him by his collar.
I can't believe you're sick.

22:11.038 --> 22:11.913
Get up.

22:13.290 --> 22:16.168
- Come on.
- That hurts.

22:16.835 --> 22:18.086
Gosh.

22:22.299 --> 22:23.383
Let me see.

22:25.093 --> 22:26.636
My goodness.

22:27.304 --> 22:30.057
You should always remember
that you're old now, all right?

22:31.099 --> 22:35.353
You should've thought things through
before jumping on him.

22:39.191 --> 22:40.442
You'll get better

22:40.525 --> 22:42.319
once you take some medicine and rest.

22:44.196 --> 22:46.531
But you need to eat first.

22:46.990 --> 22:50.035
It would be hard to get yourself up again.
Don't lie down and stay seated.

22:50.202 --> 22:52.037
I'll fix you a meal.

22:53.038 --> 22:54.539
Shouldn't I eat porridge or something?

22:57.918 --> 23:00.754
You act as if you did something grand.

23:17.270 --> 23:18.438
- Hyeon-jeong.
- Yes, ma'am.

23:18.522 --> 23:20.857
- Did you check on the condiment station?
- Yes, I already did.

23:22.317 --> 23:24.361
- Hello.
- Hello, what would you like to order?

23:24.903 --> 23:26.530
I'm from the head office.

23:28.824 --> 23:30.992
- My name is Kang Se-yeong.
- I see.

23:31.701 --> 23:32.994
You're the store owner, right?

23:33.578 --> 23:35.831
Yes, I am. What brings you here?

23:36.998 --> 23:41.419
Nothing special. I was in the area,
so I just wanted to stop by to say hello.

23:42.629 --> 23:45.549
I heard you're Ms. Yoon Jin-a's friend.

23:46.299 --> 23:48.802
- That's right.
- I've heard a lot about you.

23:48.885 --> 23:49.761
I see.

23:49.845 --> 23:53.765
You're also
Mr. Seo Jun-hui's sister, right?

23:53.849 --> 23:54.850
Yes, I am.

23:56.351 --> 24:00.564
I've met him once through Ms. Yoon.

24:01.148 --> 24:02.858
- Oh, I see.
- Yes.

24:03.775 --> 24:04.651
Since you're here,

24:04.734 --> 24:07.070
how about you try our coffee
to make sure it's good?

24:09.072 --> 24:10.407
You have a great sense of humor.

24:10.740 --> 24:12.325
That'd be great,

24:12.409 --> 24:15.287
but I'll have to pay for the coffee.

24:18.248 --> 24:20.250
Actually, you'll have to try
our coffee another time.

24:31.386 --> 24:34.764
You'll return all the supplies
you rented from the head office

24:34.848 --> 24:36.391
and sell the ones you bought, right?

24:38.268 --> 24:39.853
I'll call the collection company--

24:39.936 --> 24:43.231
Come on. Why do you rush things?

24:45.275 --> 24:49.279
You need to close the store
as soon as possible to save costs.

24:49.738 --> 24:51.823
I'm doing this for you.

24:52.032 --> 24:53.283
I never asked you for it.

24:54.993 --> 24:57.913
Thank you for your concern,

24:58.663 --> 25:01.416
but why don't we talk first?

25:01.499 --> 25:03.793
Don't you think
you're taking this matter to the extreme?

25:09.549 --> 25:11.051
I guess it's because my life is harsh.

25:16.223 --> 25:19.392
Why does life have to be so complicated?

25:20.227 --> 25:23.271
Stop it. You are still so young.

25:23.355 --> 25:24.731
Don't say things like that.

25:27.150 --> 25:30.403
Don't assume that I have an easy life
just because I'm young.

25:32.739 --> 25:36.576
I've been betrayed and hurt.

25:37.786 --> 25:40.789
Then when I find consolation in something,

25:41.373 --> 25:42.832
I pull myself together.

25:44.417 --> 25:46.836
But I eventually sink back
into despair again.

25:48.630 --> 25:53.301
Despite that, I still try to find hope.

25:55.345 --> 25:56.388
Everyone lives like that.

25:59.057 --> 26:01.059
I'm sure we all feel the same way.

26:03.979 --> 26:06.982
I know. We're all trying our best
to make ends meet.

26:10.402 --> 26:11.486
Cheer up.

26:17.909 --> 26:20.078
- You, too.
- All right.

26:28.461 --> 26:29.713
You'll work all night again?

26:31.089 --> 26:33.216
Since when did you work so hard?

26:33.300 --> 26:34.301
I've always worked hard.

26:34.926 --> 26:36.428
- Hello.
- Hello.

26:37.095 --> 26:38.847
You're missing one member today.

26:39.848 --> 26:41.516
Ms. Yoon had to go a store, so she's--

26:41.599 --> 26:42.809
She has a date tonight.

26:43.852 --> 26:45.103
- I see.
- No way.

26:45.186 --> 26:47.314
I saw her with her boyfriend.

26:47.397 --> 26:50.984
Oh, right.
I was at your sister's store earlier.

26:51.359 --> 26:52.569
I see.

26:52.944 --> 26:56.489
So one member is out on a date.
Where are you ladies headed now?

26:56.573 --> 26:57.657
We're going home.

26:58.408 --> 26:59.576
I haven't decided yet.

26:59.826 --> 27:01.119
I guess you have plans.

27:01.578 --> 27:02.871
I'm going to make plans.

27:02.954 --> 27:05.999
Jun-hui, when will you take me
to a hip club?

27:07.292 --> 27:08.251
Let's go now.

27:08.335 --> 27:10.378
You said you have to work...

27:11.671 --> 27:14.883
You must've meant
that you're going to party all night.

27:15.008 --> 27:16.551
- I'll go bring my bag.
- Me too.

27:17.177 --> 27:18.345
Are we really going clubbing?

27:18.428 --> 27:21.556
I'm not dressed for it.
I should've worn something fancier.

27:22.057 --> 27:23.433
You sound like a clubber.

27:24.434 --> 27:27.312
Bo-ra, you probably don't
want to join us, right?

27:27.437 --> 27:30.273
You should come with us.
Let's watch them have fun.

27:31.775 --> 27:32.817
Sure, I'll come.

27:35.820 --> 27:37.030
What are you talking about?

27:37.322 --> 27:40.867
Jin-a is seeing someone?
Stop spewing total nonsense.

27:42.619 --> 27:46.498
Even I saw her with him a number of times.
How can you not know?

27:47.582 --> 27:50.293
There's no way I wouldn't know
if she has been seeing someone.

27:50.668 --> 27:53.338
But I don't know about any guy,
which means you got it all wrong.

27:54.047 --> 27:56.216
She must've been hiding it from you too.

27:56.299 --> 27:57.133
Hey.

28:00.136 --> 28:03.723
You see, I saw him at her place.

28:07.018 --> 28:09.229
In front of her parents,

28:12.023 --> 28:14.025
she said that she has feelings for him.

28:16.486 --> 28:18.613
But do you want to know
what's even funnier?

28:22.200 --> 28:23.785
That guy is Seung-ho's friend.

28:25.286 --> 28:27.539
He's her brother's friend.

28:28.456 --> 28:32.585
Are you talking about the guy
who picked her up from work?

28:32.669 --> 28:36.381
So you know him too.
Why did you act like you didn't know him?

28:36.464 --> 28:38.925
Gosh, you're giving me a headache.
You idiot!

28:47.684 --> 28:50.603
I just told you that I was with him.
How did you know we'd be here?

28:51.521 --> 28:53.773
This is the only place in the area
that you would come to.

28:54.649 --> 28:55.525
Right.

28:58.153 --> 28:59.195
- Gyeong-seon.
- Yes?

28:59.279 --> 29:00.530
You should get going now.

29:13.668 --> 29:16.254
I must say, you're very aggressive today.

29:16.504 --> 29:18.131
Did you have a fight with somebody?

29:18.757 --> 29:21.092
So many people are getting on my nerves
these days.

29:22.469 --> 29:23.553
It must be tough for you.

29:24.471 --> 29:26.473
By the way, Gyu-min is so dumb.

29:26.556 --> 29:28.308
He thinks you're seeing Jun-hui.

29:29.434 --> 29:31.436
Why didn't you tell me
he saw Jun-hui at your place?

29:32.687 --> 29:35.482
Oh, I was going to tell you
about it later.

29:36.191 --> 29:39.152
Even just talking about it
annoyed me and felt like a hassle.

29:39.694 --> 29:41.279
You know how it feels

29:41.362 --> 29:44.741
when you don't even want
to talk about someone.

29:44.824 --> 29:45.992
That's why I haven't told you.

29:46.159 --> 29:48.495
I know. I get what you're trying to say.

29:49.412 --> 29:51.539
But will you really be able to handle him?

29:52.665 --> 29:54.250
I should just die if I can't.

29:54.709 --> 29:56.628
You sound very determined,
so I'll trust you.

29:57.712 --> 29:59.339
I hope you have a good closure.

30:06.888 --> 30:08.431
YE-EUN

30:08.765 --> 30:10.141
Ms. Yoon, you should come too.

30:21.319 --> 30:22.737
Thank you.

30:24.072 --> 30:25.990
Hey, Lee Gyu-min.

31:29.095 --> 31:31.472
Where did you say you're going? My home?

31:31.806 --> 31:33.182
You must have gone crazy.

31:33.266 --> 31:35.643
No, I'm not crazy.
I need to clear my name.

31:36.311 --> 31:39.147
You made me look like a total jerk,
and it's so unfair!

31:39.314 --> 31:42.108
I must meet your parents again
and tell them that you cheated on me, too.

31:42.191 --> 31:43.860
I'm going to make them apologize to me!

31:43.943 --> 31:45.737
- Hey!
- And that prick too!

31:45.820 --> 31:47.530
Seung-ho's buddy or whoever he is.

31:47.614 --> 31:50.116
I'll make him apologize to me
on his knees!

31:50.617 --> 31:53.328
Were you always this crazy?

31:53.703 --> 31:55.538
- You're one to--
- Were you always this pathetic?

31:55.622 --> 31:58.291
You're one to talk.
What are you so proud of?

31:58.374 --> 32:01.210
Did you go to a better school than me,
or is your family richer than mine?

32:07.592 --> 32:11.304
I can't believe you're making me do this.

32:53.596 --> 32:56.307
I told Ms. Yoon that we're here,
but I haven't heard anything from her.

32:59.936 --> 33:01.187
Just leave her be.

33:14.033 --> 33:15.618
I said, I'm really going to die.

33:17.412 --> 33:20.289
- I told you to go ahead.
- You think I'm just bluffing?

33:21.374 --> 33:22.625
Yes, I do.

33:25.962 --> 33:28.756
You're unbelievable.
Do you hate me that much now?

33:28.840 --> 33:30.675
Do you want me to die?

33:30.758 --> 33:32.552
Are you seriously done with me?

33:33.136 --> 33:35.179
How many more times
do I need to tell you that?

33:36.681 --> 33:38.558
It's because of that scumbag, isn't it?

33:38.641 --> 33:40.351
Stop calling him names.

33:40.935 --> 33:43.146
He doesn't deserve to be treated that way.

33:45.189 --> 33:47.066
It's not because of anyone else.

33:48.651 --> 33:52.447
I just hate myself
for having been stupid enough to love you.

33:52.739 --> 33:55.783
I really hate myself for that,
and that's all.

33:59.704 --> 34:00.621
Gyu-min.

34:01.831 --> 34:03.708
Let's not hate each other

34:04.417 --> 34:06.794
and get on with our own lives, okay?

34:07.670 --> 34:08.504
Bye.

34:13.968 --> 34:16.012
I'm never going to give up on you!

34:16.512 --> 34:19.807
I'm going to make you love me again!

34:28.566 --> 34:29.734
What's this?

34:30.902 --> 34:32.987
Wait, what were you doing?

34:33.863 --> 34:35.239
Is this a trendy move?

34:35.323 --> 34:37.992
I thought you were busy dancing.
When did you take these?

34:38.826 --> 34:41.120
You're the one who was busy dancing.

34:41.704 --> 34:44.040
You weren't eager to go,
but you enjoyed it there the most.

34:44.123 --> 34:45.041
I know.

34:45.124 --> 34:48.294
Well, I tend to give my all
to the given situation.

34:48.878 --> 34:49.879
Good morning.

34:50.379 --> 34:52.548
- Ms. Yoon, I sent you a text last night.
- Hey.

34:52.632 --> 34:54.550
How did the talk with your boyfriend go?

34:54.717 --> 34:56.427
- How did you know that?
- What?

34:56.886 --> 34:58.721
That's not important.

34:58.888 --> 35:00.890
What matters is
if you two are getting back together.

35:01.557 --> 35:02.850
So, did things work out well?

35:04.268 --> 35:06.813
I guess you could say that.

35:06.938 --> 35:08.106
No wonder.

35:08.189 --> 35:11.150
I was going to text you again,
but your friend stopped me.

35:17.615 --> 35:18.616
Yes, Mr. Jo.

35:19.408 --> 35:21.327
I was worried about the store in Gasan,

35:22.328 --> 35:23.996
but Jin-a must have taken care of it.

35:24.080 --> 35:27.917
Yes. The store owner must have acted out

35:28.000 --> 35:29.669
so that he'd get our attention.

35:30.378 --> 35:31.796
We can't just settle it at that.

35:32.421 --> 35:34.507
He's probably still very dissatisfied.

35:36.008 --> 35:38.928
But other store owners might do the same
if we go easy on him.

35:39.011 --> 35:40.805
We should make an example of him--

35:40.888 --> 35:43.099
That's not something
that can be done easily these days.

35:43.683 --> 35:44.851
You're right, sir.

35:45.226 --> 35:47.937
We should focus on keeping
the store running.

35:48.604 --> 35:50.523
We should prioritize
turning things back to normal

35:50.606 --> 35:52.525
by putting Jin-a in charge of that store.

35:52.859 --> 35:56.320
I think that's the best we can do
for the company and the store.

36:02.285 --> 36:03.786
Did you have lunch, sir?

36:05.329 --> 36:07.832
- Right, Ms. Yoon.
- Yes, sir.

36:08.040 --> 36:11.294
About what happened
regarding the opening event...

36:11.586 --> 36:12.795
You were meant to pay.

36:13.921 --> 36:16.382
I'll take care of it soon, sir.

36:16.465 --> 36:17.508
No, it's okay.

36:18.801 --> 36:20.094
I thought it was too harsh

36:21.053 --> 36:23.598
to make an employee pay for everything.

36:24.056 --> 36:25.933
So the company will cover the expenses.

36:26.017 --> 36:29.520
I already settled it that way,
so keep that in mind.

36:30.104 --> 36:34.025
Mr. Nam, I respect you for caring
so much about your employees.

36:34.275 --> 36:35.401
It's nothing.

36:36.027 --> 36:37.486
What are you doing?

36:37.570 --> 36:38.988
You should be grateful.

36:39.363 --> 36:42.366
- Well...
- That's not necessary. It's okay.

36:43.409 --> 36:44.911
Thank you, Mr. Nam.

36:56.714 --> 36:57.924
You covered for me, didn't you?

36:58.132 --> 36:59.592
Regarding the expenses...

37:01.385 --> 37:02.803
I have no power to cover for you.

37:03.346 --> 37:04.764
We just followed the company policy.

37:06.098 --> 37:08.601
Come on. I've been around long enough.

37:08.851 --> 37:10.353
I know at least that much.

37:10.978 --> 37:13.064
I suggest you go back to your desk

37:13.773 --> 37:15.191
before others start talking.

37:15.775 --> 37:18.569
Thank you for always helping me out.

37:19.237 --> 37:21.030
I'm not just helping you.

37:23.574 --> 37:25.618
Then I guess you won't be working
at the office.

37:26.035 --> 37:28.955
Yes, I'll be working at the store.

37:29.622 --> 37:34.001
Your store will be managed
by someone named Kang Se-yeong...

37:34.502 --> 37:35.795
I know who she is.

37:36.337 --> 37:39.048
She was here
when Gyu-min barged in yesterday.

37:41.425 --> 37:42.635
She's quick.

37:42.718 --> 37:44.679
- What do you mean?
- It's nothing.

37:46.389 --> 37:49.600
She's good at what she does,
so she won't cause trouble regarding work.

37:50.434 --> 37:52.979
Does that mean I should watch out
for other things?

37:55.314 --> 37:56.315
I'm just saying.

38:00.528 --> 38:03.823
Are you jealous that I might become
better friends with her?

38:04.824 --> 38:07.076
That's not true, Your Highness.

38:07.159 --> 38:09.787
I'm hungry. Let's go eat. I'll buy.

38:09.870 --> 38:12.623
Next time.
Today's the anniversary of my mom's death.

38:14.041 --> 38:16.544
Was it today? I totally forgot.

38:16.752 --> 38:19.797
It's fine.
Let's go grocery shopping together.

38:19.880 --> 38:21.507
- I'll go get my purse.
- Okay.

38:24.760 --> 38:26.429
Time flies by so fast.

38:26.637 --> 38:28.472
It's already been ten years.

38:29.056 --> 38:30.016
Right.

38:30.516 --> 38:32.977
She passed away after Jun-hui took
his college entrance exam.

38:34.687 --> 38:36.522
It was really cold that day.

38:37.189 --> 38:39.233
I know. It was.

38:41.819 --> 38:44.655
Haven't you heard from your dad?

38:45.573 --> 38:46.866
I'm scared he might call

38:47.491 --> 38:50.619
and ask us if he could come back to us.

38:51.787 --> 38:54.623
You seem really strong-minded at times.

38:55.791 --> 38:57.585
That's how I survived.

38:57.752 --> 39:01.797
It wasn't easy growing up with Jun-hui
without our parents.

39:09.180 --> 39:11.390
When I go to heaven and meet my mom,

39:11.474 --> 39:13.684
I'm going to ask her to pay me good money

39:14.393 --> 39:16.645
for having raised her son so well.

39:17.938 --> 39:19.231
Don't I deserve that much?

39:19.690 --> 39:22.860
Of course. You raised him very well.

39:23.778 --> 39:26.113
I don't know whom he'll end up marrying,

39:26.197 --> 39:28.491
but I'm going to be a mean sister-in-law.

39:33.120 --> 39:34.705
I can't let her have him under her thumb.

39:34.789 --> 39:36.457
I'll show her who's the boss
from the start.

39:37.792 --> 39:40.836
Hey, I already feel bad
for his future wife.

39:40.920 --> 39:43.589
It'll be fun. All you have to do
is watch from the sidelines.

39:45.091 --> 39:46.050
Right.

39:46.592 --> 39:48.761
Are you completely done with Gyu-min?

39:49.053 --> 39:50.179
Let's not talk about him.

39:50.262 --> 39:51.806
- Let me ask you one more thing.
- What?

39:52.014 --> 39:53.849
How dumb does he have to be

39:53.933 --> 39:55.768
to believe that you and Jun-hui
are a thing?

39:55.851 --> 39:57.645
It was so hilarious.

39:57.978 --> 39:59.105
Isn't it funny?

40:01.315 --> 40:04.110
- I know.
- Pork neck is only 1,000 won.

40:05.611 --> 40:07.696
Pork neck is only 1,000 won.

40:11.075 --> 40:12.660
It's still rush hour,

40:12.743 --> 40:14.870
so we might not be able to get a taxi.

40:15.329 --> 40:16.789
Jun-hui will be here.

40:44.024 --> 40:45.401
Do you want to sit in the front?

40:45.818 --> 40:47.361
No, I'll just go from here.

40:47.445 --> 40:49.572
Your place is nearby. We'll drop you off.

40:49.655 --> 40:51.240
You should go and cook.

40:51.323 --> 40:52.992
I'll put the cart back.

40:53.075 --> 40:53.909
Hey.

40:54.326 --> 40:55.369
That brat.

40:56.996 --> 41:00.332
Hey, you could have offered her a ride.

41:00.708 --> 41:03.085
- She already refused.
- You jerk.

41:11.510 --> 41:13.637
Are you still upset
about what happened a few days ago?

41:14.680 --> 41:16.640
What is it? Why the long face?

41:17.808 --> 41:18.893
I'm fine.

41:20.978 --> 41:22.855
Did Jin-a come to your store?

41:23.063 --> 41:23.939
Yes.

41:24.940 --> 41:27.485
She'll be working
at some other store temporarily.

41:29.028 --> 41:30.821
The head office
tried to close that store down.

41:30.905 --> 41:33.741
I bet she felt bad to let that happen.
It's so typical of her.

41:34.241 --> 41:37.703
I'm not surprised that she couldn't
end things with Gyu-min easily.

41:39.455 --> 41:42.166
I heard you went to her place.
Why didn't you tell me?

41:43.792 --> 41:45.127
I didn't have a chance.

41:47.671 --> 41:48.589
Did she tell you?

41:49.465 --> 41:52.384
No, Gyu-min came to see me.

41:52.968 --> 41:54.678
He was a mess.

41:56.180 --> 41:58.098
He came to see you? When?

41:58.349 --> 41:59.266
Yesterday.

42:00.518 --> 42:03.437
An employee from the head office
was there. What was her name?

42:04.104 --> 42:05.272
Right, Kang Se-yeong.

42:05.898 --> 42:09.026
I was talking with her when he showed up.

42:09.318 --> 42:11.445
Jin-a came right away.

42:12.196 --> 42:15.157
They must have had a huge fight.
Jin-a was furious.

42:18.786 --> 42:19.954
I'm worried about her.

42:20.704 --> 42:23.582
I wish Jin-a lived near my place.

42:24.583 --> 42:27.086
Remember the day you came home upset
and went out after?

42:27.503 --> 42:29.046
I went to your place to steal more beer.

42:30.214 --> 42:32.424
Someone was at the door, so I went out.
It was Jin-a.

42:33.133 --> 42:34.260
She came to my place?

42:34.510 --> 42:37.054
She couldn't find me.
She figured I was with you.

42:37.763 --> 42:38.973
Make a right.

42:39.807 --> 42:40.975
Oh, right...

42:43.018 --> 42:44.270
Where's your head at?

42:51.193 --> 42:52.820
I'm home.

42:52.903 --> 42:53.904
Hi.

43:01.120 --> 43:02.913
Where did you get these fruits?

43:03.706 --> 43:04.915
Gyeong-seon gave them to me.

43:05.374 --> 43:06.542
We went shopping together

43:06.625 --> 43:08.335
since her mother's memorial service
is today.

43:08.419 --> 43:10.087
- Those are for you.
- Gosh.

43:10.588 --> 43:13.007
This is why I think of her
as my own daughter.

43:15.509 --> 43:18.262
- Come sit here for a minute.
- Why?

43:18.345 --> 43:19.388
Take a seat.

43:21.098 --> 43:24.351
Are you completely over with Gyu-min?

43:24.435 --> 43:25.978
- Mom.
- Look.

43:26.395 --> 43:31.233
I know it's entirely Gyu-min's fault.
He shouldn't have done that, but...

43:31.817 --> 43:34.153
Why can't you just give up on him?

43:35.404 --> 43:38.198
Is it because of his academic background?
Or his prestigious family?

43:40.159 --> 43:41.493
What do you take me for?

43:41.869 --> 43:45.998
I'm saying that you should date
someone better than him in the future.

43:46.373 --> 43:49.293
Don't let superficial things fool you.

43:51.003 --> 43:52.087
That won't happen.

43:53.881 --> 43:57.092
You promised. You'd better keep it.

44:44.431 --> 44:46.266
What would she think of us?

44:48.811 --> 44:50.145
She would be proud of you,

44:51.146 --> 44:54.149
and I'm sure she would think
I'm way too handsome.

45:57.087 --> 45:59.631
Jin-a loves this.

46:00.215 --> 46:01.508
I should've invited her over.

46:03.510 --> 46:05.387
People might think she's your daughter.

46:08.223 --> 46:11.935
Sometimes, she feels like my daughter
or even my mother.

46:13.520 --> 46:15.189
When Dad got remarried

46:16.356 --> 46:19.860
and we were left by ourselves,
whom do you think I relied on?

46:22.237 --> 46:24.114
I couldn't rely on my little brother.

46:26.283 --> 46:29.661
Jin-a was the one
who was always there for me.

46:30.704 --> 46:33.248
Not even a real sister could do that much.

46:41.215 --> 46:43.884
I have two goals left in life.
Guess what they are.

46:48.430 --> 46:52.184
One must be related to me, whatever it is.

46:54.269 --> 46:55.604
I don't know about the other one.

46:56.188 --> 46:58.106
To make sure Jin-a marries a good guy.

47:01.401 --> 47:04.029
Just talking about her makes me miss her.

47:05.697 --> 47:08.242
Let's see what she is up to.

47:16.583 --> 47:17.876
Hello.

47:19.044 --> 47:20.546
What are you up to?

47:23.173 --> 47:26.218
Letting go of your past?
Deleting your memory?

47:33.183 --> 47:35.769
What? You're throwing them all out?

47:36.478 --> 47:39.982
You're wasting money again.
You're being ridiculous.

47:40.983 --> 47:41.817
Listen.

47:42.359 --> 47:43.819
The clothes didn't do anything wrong.

47:49.783 --> 47:51.159
All right.

47:53.453 --> 47:55.581
Fine. Okay.

49:14.826 --> 49:15.869
What...

49:16.703 --> 49:18.163
What are you doing here?

49:19.706 --> 49:20.749
I heard you came by.

49:24.252 --> 49:25.087
Why did you come by?

49:28.799 --> 49:30.592
Is that all Gyeong-seon said?

49:31.426 --> 49:35.222
She should've told you everything.
Why did she leave some things out?

49:35.722 --> 49:39.351
I went over to her place,
but she wasn't there.

49:39.768 --> 49:42.646
So I went looking for her at your place,
and she was there.

49:46.483 --> 49:47.859
Were you really looking for her?

49:49.653 --> 49:51.321
Who else would I look for?

49:54.491 --> 49:56.493
I'm asking you if you came by to see me.

49:59.913 --> 50:01.289
I mean...

50:04.793 --> 50:05.836
Fine.

50:06.795 --> 50:08.213
I went to see you.

50:10.006 --> 50:13.051
I wanted to apologize and thank you.

50:13.719 --> 50:17.931
But you kept going on
about what I did wrong.

50:18.265 --> 50:20.559
I was glad I didn't talk to you that day.

50:21.184 --> 50:24.771
It would've been embarrassing
to hear that in front of Gyeong-seon.

50:24.855 --> 50:27.482
What's so embarrassing?
Everything I said is true.

50:31.695 --> 50:35.282
Why did you show up here
and start getting on my nerves?

50:35.365 --> 50:37.743
- Do I look like a pushover?
- That's it.

50:38.243 --> 50:41.705
Why were you a pushover to him
and let him treat you that way?

50:41.788 --> 50:42.664
Why...

50:42.748 --> 50:44.666
Why would you let someone like him
do that to you?

50:44.750 --> 50:46.752
I wasn't a pushover.

50:47.252 --> 50:51.381
Gosh, I just can't help but laugh.
You're being ridiculous.

50:51.965 --> 50:53.925
You're not laughing.
What's so ridiculous about it?

50:58.263 --> 50:59.765
Fine. Let's say you are right.

50:59.890 --> 51:01.349
You have nothing more to say, right?

51:01.516 --> 51:02.559
I do.

51:08.315 --> 51:09.524
What's with the umbrella?

51:13.862 --> 51:16.364
I brought it since it might rain. Why?

51:17.741 --> 51:20.619
I thought you were throwing things away
for a fresh start.

51:21.077 --> 51:22.162
Is this part of it?

51:24.581 --> 51:27.626
- Give it to me. I'll throw it away.
- Don't. I took it back from...

51:30.545 --> 51:31.713
You took it back?

51:36.009 --> 51:37.552
- You must like that umbrella.
- Gosh,

51:37.636 --> 51:39.346
- you little...
- Hey.

51:40.889 --> 51:42.808
- Keep it then.
- Get over here.

51:44.726 --> 51:46.520
Stop teasing me.

51:47.062 --> 51:48.021
Punk.

51:50.482 --> 51:51.566
Are you mad at me?

52:15.966 --> 52:16.967
Do you have to go home?

52:18.927 --> 52:20.011
Where else would we go?

52:24.099 --> 52:25.350
What did you just think of?

52:27.769 --> 52:29.312
Nothing at all.

52:31.523 --> 52:32.858
What?

52:33.859 --> 52:35.068
Never mind.

52:37.737 --> 52:38.655
Let's go have fun.

52:40.949 --> 52:41.783
Okay.

52:47.122 --> 52:49.499
- Do you want to eat something?
- No.

52:50.417 --> 52:51.626
Why not? Let's drink some coke.

52:51.918 --> 52:54.880
I feel sorry for making you pay.
I didn't even bring my wallet.

52:55.797 --> 52:57.716
That means you can't go home without me.

52:57.799 --> 52:59.843
Gosh, you got me again.

52:59.926 --> 53:01.303
I'll use it to my benefit.

53:01.720 --> 53:03.054
I'll buy you coke.

53:03.680 --> 53:05.390
Then can you buy me some popcorn as well?

53:46.890 --> 53:48.850
- That's mine.
- What?

53:51.686 --> 53:52.854
Oh, you're right.

54:04.074 --> 54:06.201
Thank you for watching.

54:08.620 --> 54:09.537
Thank you.

54:09.788 --> 54:11.122
The movie was good.

54:11.957 --> 54:13.667
You weren't watching the movie.

54:15.669 --> 54:16.962
Were you watching the same thing?

54:17.504 --> 54:18.505
No.

54:21.132 --> 54:22.175
Aren't you hungry?

54:22.926 --> 54:23.885
I am.

54:24.886 --> 54:27.722
Then say, "Please buy me something tasty."

54:28.890 --> 54:30.058
Do you want to die?

54:30.934 --> 54:32.060
Give that to me.

54:33.269 --> 54:34.813
Are you going to buy me food?

54:35.647 --> 54:36.731
Are you going to?

54:52.205 --> 54:53.748
He drew them so well.

54:59.921 --> 55:02.507
You can't compliment
other people's drawings in front of me.

55:05.176 --> 55:07.679
I'm sorry. I didn't know.

55:10.140 --> 55:11.891
I guess I should show you what I've got.

55:25.530 --> 55:26.781
Is this too Rodin for you?

55:45.633 --> 55:46.760
The model's not very...

56:42.482 --> 56:43.858
When will you be done?

56:44.484 --> 56:45.610
This is so hard.

56:46.111 --> 56:48.071
There's nothing special about the subject.

56:48.822 --> 56:50.115
There's nothing to emphasize.

56:50.365 --> 56:51.783
Then don't draw me.

56:52.700 --> 56:54.744
- I'm done.
- Let me see.

56:57.997 --> 56:58.957
Pay me first.

56:59.874 --> 57:01.835
I said I don't have money.

57:02.001 --> 57:03.503
It doesn't have to be money.

57:03.586 --> 57:04.462
Then what?

57:05.755 --> 57:08.174
I really didn't bring anything.

57:11.845 --> 57:13.304
- I have something.
- What?

57:15.056 --> 57:16.307
My beauty?

57:16.891 --> 57:18.309
My gosh. Here.

57:20.270 --> 57:21.312
Let's see.

57:26.359 --> 57:27.902
Is this how I look?

57:29.571 --> 57:30.989
You look exactly like this.

57:31.072 --> 57:33.324
This is practically a photo.

57:33.741 --> 57:35.577
Is this what my body looks like?

57:36.077 --> 57:38.705
Yes, you're really petite.

57:38.955 --> 57:39.831
Hey.

57:40.874 --> 57:42.834
This is exaggerated.

57:43.251 --> 57:46.463
This is how you look.
You're so tiny and cute.

57:49.841 --> 57:50.967
I'm not cute.

57:52.594 --> 57:54.637
Have you forgotten how old I am?

57:56.264 --> 58:00.310
Some might still find you cute
regardless of your age.

58:01.603 --> 58:04.689
Well, I guess you have a point.

58:05.607 --> 58:09.027
But still, I'm too old to be called cute.

58:10.153 --> 58:11.821
But people used to say that about me a lot

58:12.405 --> 58:14.365
when I was in my 20s.

58:17.035 --> 58:18.870
I knew you back then.

58:18.953 --> 58:20.205
You weren't that cute.

58:21.581 --> 58:23.917
You're right. You know my past.

58:24.125 --> 58:25.502
Then forget it.

58:28.296 --> 58:30.715
Come to think of it, you were cute.

58:30.798 --> 58:32.634
Right. You were cute.

58:33.134 --> 58:35.803
You looked like that actress...

58:37.138 --> 58:39.057
I promise I will pay you back
ten times over

58:39.140 --> 58:42.268
for everything you bought me today.

58:43.311 --> 58:44.896
You'd better prepare yourself.

58:45.188 --> 58:47.440
I'm going to take everything from you.

58:48.274 --> 58:49.692
Don't take my clothes.

58:50.318 --> 58:53.488
My gosh, you have a perverted mind.

58:54.322 --> 58:57.116
I was just joking.

59:02.997 --> 59:04.415
If you were letting go of your past,

59:05.208 --> 59:09.420
does that mean
you thought me as someone from your past?

59:11.130 --> 59:12.674
What do you mean?

59:14.425 --> 59:19.055
I mean, why exactly were you trying
to throw this out with other things?

59:19.931 --> 59:21.891
What are you talking about?

59:22.016 --> 59:24.936
I just absent-mindedly brought it with me.

59:26.771 --> 59:28.690
That's not what you said earlier.

59:30.108 --> 59:32.110
I was going to use it if it rained

59:32.193 --> 59:34.112
and not use it if it didn't.

59:34.362 --> 59:37.448
That's what umbrellas are for.
Does there have to be a meaning?

59:41.494 --> 59:43.413
No, not really.

59:45.331 --> 59:47.166
Just don't throw it away.

59:48.668 --> 59:50.003
I never said I will.

59:51.713 --> 59:52.714
What if you do?

59:53.172 --> 59:54.841
I'll never throw it away.

59:56.426 --> 59:57.802
Why "never"?

59:59.554 --> 01:00:02.223
You're making a big deal out of nothing.

01:00:02.307 --> 01:00:03.975
What do you want?

01:00:04.976 --> 01:00:06.352
Keep it well.

01:00:07.103 --> 01:00:08.062
Fine.

01:00:33.504 --> 01:00:34.964
I should go now.

01:00:35.548 --> 01:00:36.591
What are you going to do?

01:00:38.968 --> 01:00:39.886
What?

01:00:41.095 --> 01:00:42.221
Are you going to sleep?

01:00:44.390 --> 01:00:45.600
Not right away.

01:00:46.184 --> 01:00:48.019
Why? What about you?

01:00:50.355 --> 01:00:51.731
What should I do?

01:00:52.899 --> 01:00:54.525
I don't know. What do you want to do?

01:00:58.988 --> 01:01:00.531
Do you want to do it together?

01:01:06.537 --> 01:01:07.622
My gosh.

01:01:09.123 --> 01:01:11.250
- Gosh. No, no.
- Oh, no.

01:01:11.334 --> 01:01:13.336
Where am I supposed to go? Is this right?

01:01:13.920 --> 01:01:16.214
- Just stay there.
- Okay.

01:01:18.966 --> 01:01:20.426
Hey, I'll go. Just stay there.

01:01:21.427 --> 01:01:22.595
Yes.

01:01:24.097 --> 01:01:25.431
Oh, no.

01:01:26.057 --> 01:01:27.183
Follow me.

01:01:28.017 --> 01:01:29.894
I'm going. Wait up.

01:01:30.436 --> 01:01:32.105
I'll show you what I've got.

01:01:35.608 --> 01:01:36.984
Are you coming?

01:01:38.986 --> 01:01:39.904
Come on.

01:01:41.364 --> 01:01:42.573
You're following me, right?

01:03:16.667 --> 01:03:19.253
How long will you be working
at the Gasan store?

01:03:19.420 --> 01:03:21.672
It's not decided yet.
Take good care of my stores.

01:03:21.756 --> 01:03:23.257
I'll treat you when I'm back.

01:03:23.758 --> 01:03:27.053
I'll be looking forward to it.
I should get going now.

01:03:27.178 --> 01:03:28.471
Okay, have a good day.

01:03:32.600 --> 01:03:34.477
Bo-ra, I assigned you to only two stores

01:03:34.602 --> 01:03:36.562
that are close to the ones
you're in charge of.

01:03:37.730 --> 01:03:39.357
Am I supposed to be grateful for it?

01:03:40.525 --> 01:03:42.068
Why are you being like that?

01:03:42.318 --> 01:03:44.403
It's not like Jin-a had a choice
in this matter.

01:03:45.613 --> 01:03:49.325
So? Is there anything I need to know
about the Suseo store?

01:03:49.617 --> 01:03:52.578
Any requests from the owner or anything
about the store owner's preference?

01:03:52.662 --> 01:03:56.123
Why are you asking her?
Ask the owner's brother directly.

01:03:58.501 --> 01:04:00.628
I must say, Bo-ra is so smart.

01:04:02.588 --> 01:04:03.965
You have to treat me big-time.

01:04:04.715 --> 01:04:06.092
Sure thing.

01:04:06.759 --> 01:04:08.636
It looks like she should be treating you.

01:04:08.719 --> 01:04:10.471
She's excited to oversee the Suseo store.

01:04:11.055 --> 01:04:13.099
It'll be great if that means
she'll do a good job.

01:04:13.724 --> 01:04:15.268
It's obviously not because of work.

01:04:15.351 --> 01:04:18.312
She's trying to get things going
with Mr. Seo.

01:04:18.938 --> 01:04:21.190
Why do you not want things to go well
between those two?

01:04:22.483 --> 01:04:23.693
I'm not against it, but...

01:04:24.485 --> 01:04:27.196
How would you feel if Ms. Kang
dates your brother?

01:04:27.613 --> 01:04:29.198
- My brother?
- Yes.

01:04:29.699 --> 01:04:32.118
That's crazy.
What kind of nonsense is that?

01:04:32.201 --> 01:04:35.371
See? Mr. Seo is your friend's brother,

01:04:35.788 --> 01:04:38.082
so isn't he like a brother to you?

01:04:41.460 --> 01:04:43.087
That is true,

01:04:43.754 --> 01:04:46.132
but my brother is my brother,

01:04:46.215 --> 01:04:48.843
whereas my friend's brother
isn't really my brother.

01:04:49.135 --> 01:04:50.636
It's different.

01:04:53.931 --> 01:04:55.349
Which coffee beans do we have now?

01:04:59.061 --> 01:05:00.187
I'll see you later.

01:05:05.234 --> 01:05:07.612
This is delicious. It's really good.

01:05:08.404 --> 01:05:11.365
Is it? I didn't even pay much attention
when I was brewing it.

01:05:12.033 --> 01:05:13.159
And it tastes this amazing?

01:05:14.118 --> 01:05:15.745
You're obviously an expert.

01:05:16.662 --> 01:05:17.747
That's right.

01:05:33.596 --> 01:05:35.806
Who the heck did this?

01:05:39.393 --> 01:05:40.519
Hang on.

01:05:40.603 --> 01:05:44.357
Action scenes where characters fight
or smash everything

01:05:44.440 --> 01:05:45.816
aren't enough these days.

01:05:46.859 --> 01:05:48.611
Then how about we try something different?

01:05:48.778 --> 01:05:52.281
For example, items like
crossbows or hammers...

01:05:52.365 --> 01:05:55.201
Crossbows and hammers? They're classics.

01:05:55.660 --> 01:05:58.162
Isn't that what Jun-hui
was talking about a while ago?

01:05:58.537 --> 01:05:59.872
Yes, sort of.

01:06:01.916 --> 01:06:02.959
Hey.

01:06:04.460 --> 01:06:05.503
Are you feeling sick?

01:06:08.297 --> 01:06:12.635
I keep feeling nauseous for some reason,
and I have a splitting headache.

01:06:12.760 --> 01:06:14.095
I feel under the weather.

01:06:14.804 --> 01:06:16.806
Hey, you should take this.

01:06:17.932 --> 01:06:18.849
Thank you.

01:06:19.850 --> 01:06:21.602
You should go see a doctor.

01:06:22.520 --> 01:06:24.730
I guess I should.
I'll be back in a bit, then.

01:06:34.740 --> 01:06:35.783
Well...

01:06:36.742 --> 01:06:38.869
Didn't he say that he is sick
a few seconds ago?

01:06:40.371 --> 01:06:41.664
He did.

01:06:51.132 --> 01:06:53.217
I could've just taken a taxi.

01:06:53.342 --> 01:06:54.802
Aren't you busy at work?

01:06:54.885 --> 01:06:57.596
No, don't worry.
I left after the meeting, so it's fine.

01:06:58.472 --> 01:06:59.557
I'm competent, you know.

01:07:00.224 --> 01:07:02.351
The company can't function without me.

01:07:03.185 --> 01:07:05.104
Is that so? I did not know that.

01:07:05.688 --> 01:07:06.689
You didn't know?

01:07:07.648 --> 01:07:09.358
You have no idea
how to spot a competent man.

01:07:10.609 --> 01:07:11.902
I don't consider you a man.

01:07:15.489 --> 01:07:17.241
It was just a figure of speech.

01:07:18.200 --> 01:07:19.910
You didn't have to point it out like that.

01:07:21.829 --> 01:07:24.540
Well, that is not what I was trying to do.

01:07:25.833 --> 01:07:28.419
You are a man. You are, aren't you?

01:07:29.462 --> 01:07:30.504
What are you saying?

01:07:31.505 --> 01:07:32.631
What time will you be done?

01:07:32.715 --> 01:07:33.632
You mean later?

01:07:33.716 --> 01:07:36.635
I don't officially start until tomorrow,

01:07:36.969 --> 01:07:38.679
so I can leave anytime. Why do you ask?

01:07:40.097 --> 01:07:41.432
I'll pick you up.

01:07:41.932 --> 01:07:45.102
Seriously? Gosh, don't bother.

01:07:47.563 --> 01:07:48.647
Will you really do that?

01:07:49.565 --> 01:07:50.691
My gosh.

01:07:50.775 --> 01:07:53.194
You'll have to open the store earlier
starting tomorrow,

01:07:53.277 --> 01:07:54.904
so please don't drink and go to bed early.

01:07:55.404 --> 01:07:57.823
I'll take care of ordering
ingredients and supplies you need.

01:07:57.907 --> 01:08:00.034
It looks like you're the store owner.

01:08:00.618 --> 01:08:03.079
Is it okay to make a head office employee
work this hard for me?

01:08:03.162 --> 01:08:04.705
You can't afford to worry about me.

01:08:04.789 --> 01:08:06.957
We can do this. Let's go!

01:08:07.416 --> 01:08:08.501
Yes, we can do this.

01:08:09.627 --> 01:08:11.587
I must say, you look chipper today.

01:08:12.755 --> 01:08:14.715
Do I? Really?

01:08:14.924 --> 01:08:16.550
You almost look like a different person.

01:08:17.259 --> 01:08:19.512
Is it because of that guy outside?

01:08:22.973 --> 01:08:25.768
I should get going. I'll see you tomorrow.

01:09:19.613 --> 01:09:20.823
Jin-a, I was just wondering...

01:09:25.369 --> 01:09:26.412
If...

01:09:29.790 --> 01:09:31.125
"If"?

01:09:34.503 --> 01:09:35.796
If I ask you...

01:09:37.840 --> 01:09:38.716
Ask me what?

01:09:41.719 --> 01:09:43.470
Well, I mean...

01:09:45.472 --> 01:09:47.683
I was just wondering...

01:09:50.394 --> 01:09:51.562
If I ask you...

01:09:55.399 --> 01:09:57.526
to treat me to a meal tomorrow, would you?

01:10:01.572 --> 01:10:03.449
I always take you out for meals.

01:10:03.991 --> 01:10:06.452
Yes, I'll treat you. You can pig out.

01:10:10.748 --> 01:10:11.749
Are you sure?

01:10:13.334 --> 01:10:14.293
Of course.

01:10:15.753 --> 01:10:16.837
All right, then.

01:13:18.852 --> 01:13:20.062
We're already here.

01:13:21.063 --> 01:13:22.189
Yes, we are.

01:13:23.649 --> 01:13:25.192
I had fun today.

01:13:28.070 --> 01:13:29.947
I could've made it more fun.

01:13:30.906 --> 01:13:32.658
It's not like I won't see you again.

01:13:33.283 --> 01:13:34.326
I know, right?

01:13:38.330 --> 01:13:40.666
- Well, I should go in.
- Sure.

01:13:49.425 --> 01:13:50.426
Bye.

01:14:33.469 --> 01:14:36.180
- Here you go, Ms. Lee.
- Thank you.

01:14:36.513 --> 01:14:38.432
It's busy even during off-peak hours.

01:14:38.515 --> 01:14:40.601
You and the store owner
must be compatible.

01:14:41.185 --> 01:14:42.978
That sounds weird.

01:14:43.061 --> 01:14:45.147
I'm just saying the two of you
met at the perfect time.

01:14:45.230 --> 01:14:47.149
Even romantic relationships
are all about timing.

01:14:47.232 --> 01:14:48.942
But the problem is that
guys always ruin it

01:14:49.026 --> 01:14:50.527
because they're so clueless.

01:14:51.320 --> 01:14:52.196
You're right.

01:14:53.113 --> 01:14:54.907
Yes, I think it's so true.

01:14:55.449 --> 01:14:57.284
But what if we keep missing
the right time?

01:14:57.367 --> 01:14:58.952
Do we have to wait until it happens?

01:14:59.119 --> 01:15:01.830
Then you'd either grow old
and die alone or get frustrated to death.

01:15:03.081 --> 01:15:05.375
It'll not work out if you wait
until things seem certain.

01:15:06.168 --> 01:15:09.129
Why? Even if you know
that you have feelings for each other?

01:15:09.546 --> 01:15:11.882
Knowing that is one thing,
but what if you're so frustrated?

01:15:12.466 --> 01:15:14.551
Let's say another guy starts
hitting on you right then.

01:15:14.843 --> 01:15:16.887
There's something fresh about him.
He's a new face.

01:15:17.429 --> 01:15:19.097
You'll fall head over heels
for the new guy.

01:15:21.391 --> 01:15:23.852
- Timing really is everything.
- Yes.

01:15:25.020 --> 01:15:26.855
CUP NOODLES

01:15:27.773 --> 01:15:30.067
GIMBAP

01:15:30.150 --> 01:15:32.319
BUDAE JJIGAE

01:15:32.402 --> 01:15:34.196
TTEOKBOKKI

01:15:34.279 --> 01:15:35.948
RAMYEON WITH RICE CAKES

01:15:36.281 --> 01:15:38.450
PORK BELLY

01:15:38.534 --> 01:15:41.078
FRIED CHICKEN

01:15:41.161 --> 01:15:42.037
I'm ready.

01:15:44.206 --> 01:15:45.290
Hurry up and shoot.

01:15:47.793 --> 01:15:49.419
- What is it?
- Which one did he get?

01:15:49.503 --> 01:15:50.754
That's good enough.

01:15:50.837 --> 01:15:52.422
- Is it rib eye?
- It's good enough.

01:15:53.298 --> 01:15:55.217
Nice, good job. Mr. Park, nicely done.

01:15:55.300 --> 01:15:56.426
- It's octopus.
- Great work.

01:15:56.510 --> 01:15:58.512
- No, I want meat.
- Octopus is great.

01:15:58.595 --> 01:16:01.265
- I'm targeting rib eye.
- This is amazing.

01:16:01.348 --> 01:16:03.684
- Take it easy.
- You need to calm down.

01:16:06.103 --> 01:16:08.188
- Pass! Next person.
- Go back in line. It's my turn.

01:16:08.272 --> 01:16:09.231
Do I have to stand here?

01:16:10.482 --> 01:16:11.483
What's he trying to shoot?

01:16:11.567 --> 01:16:13.402
- Go for rib eye.
- Rib eye.

01:16:13.485 --> 01:16:15.195
- Rib eye? Hey.
- Rib eye.

01:16:15.279 --> 01:16:17.948
- No way.
- It's impossible to shoot that.

01:16:21.660 --> 01:16:22.578
- My gosh!
- You did it!

01:16:23.287 --> 01:16:25.914
- You did it!
- Gosh, I can't believe this!

01:16:27.040 --> 01:16:29.126
Gosh, how did that happen? Let's go, guys.

01:16:30.002 --> 01:16:31.795
- Come on.
- Thank you in advance.

01:16:32.379 --> 01:16:34.423
- Would you like to take this?
- No, thanks.

01:16:34.506 --> 01:16:36.216
I got rib eye, right?

01:16:36.300 --> 01:16:38.093
Sir, he really shot rib eye.

01:16:44.099 --> 01:16:45.851
I have to go to the office in the evening.

01:16:55.152 --> 01:16:56.111
Are you still working?

01:16:58.238 --> 01:16:59.990
My team dinner will be over soon.

01:17:01.283 --> 01:17:02.743
How late will you stay at the office?

01:17:05.329 --> 01:17:08.123
I still have things to finish off,
so it'll be a while.

01:17:08.332 --> 01:17:10.042
Who keeps messaging you?

01:17:11.585 --> 01:17:13.420
Oh, it's just a friend.

01:17:14.546 --> 01:17:15.672
The owner of the Suseo store?

01:17:15.964 --> 01:17:17.090
Is it Jun-hui's sister?

01:17:19.092 --> 01:17:20.385
No, it's a different friend.

01:17:25.515 --> 01:17:26.683
You're done, right?

01:17:26.933 --> 01:17:29.269
I'm hungry.
Let's grab something to eat together.

01:17:29.978 --> 01:17:31.313
You know you owe me a meal.

01:17:33.106 --> 01:17:36.526
I still have a bit of work to finish off.

01:17:38.153 --> 01:17:39.946
What do you have to do
other than the report?

01:17:42.240 --> 01:17:43.283
You already finished it.

01:17:43.992 --> 01:17:45.243
What's with you?

01:17:45.327 --> 01:17:46.703
I guess you don't want to treat me.

01:17:47.287 --> 01:17:49.122
Let's go. I'll treat you.

01:17:53.710 --> 01:17:54.961
Here you go.

01:17:55.045 --> 01:17:56.546
- Thank you.
- Thank you for the dinner.

01:17:58.340 --> 01:17:59.549
I'm so full now.

01:18:00.050 --> 01:18:01.718
Let's go for drinks another time.

01:18:01.927 --> 01:18:03.679
What? It's not like
you'll pay for our drinks.

01:18:04.179 --> 01:18:05.389
That's not my point.

01:18:05.472 --> 01:18:07.432
Why do you want to have all the fun today?

01:18:08.725 --> 01:18:09.559
Hey,

01:18:10.560 --> 01:18:11.853
isn't she that pretty girl

01:18:11.937 --> 01:18:13.480
- at the coffee company?
- Where?

01:18:14.147 --> 01:18:15.148
Yes, it's her.

01:18:16.525 --> 01:18:17.401
Jin-a.

01:18:17.651 --> 01:18:19.444
- Hello.
- Hello.

01:18:20.946 --> 01:18:23.407
- Where are you going?
- To have dinner.

01:18:24.116 --> 01:18:25.575
I guess you're out for a team dinner.

01:18:25.659 --> 01:18:27.369
Yes, with a few members of my team.

01:18:28.328 --> 01:18:29.454
Where will you have dinner?

01:18:29.538 --> 01:18:32.249
- Somewhere around here, I guess.
- We're looking for a place to eat.

01:18:33.500 --> 01:18:37.671
But you must've eaten already.

01:18:40.340 --> 01:18:41.466
We're actually...

01:18:42.342 --> 01:18:44.052
headed to a pub for drinks.

01:18:44.177 --> 01:18:45.220
I guess you can't join us

01:18:45.303 --> 01:18:46.972
because you can't have
a proper meal there.

01:18:47.556 --> 01:18:49.516
Well, what should we do?

01:18:49.599 --> 01:18:51.518
We didn't really want to have a meal,
you know.

01:18:51.768 --> 01:18:52.686
Aren't I right?

01:18:54.563 --> 01:18:57.399
So many people think that about me,

01:18:57.482 --> 01:18:59.276
but it's not true at all.

01:18:59.693 --> 01:19:01.737
I've only dated a couple of guys.

01:19:03.613 --> 01:19:05.365
But Jin-a has a lot of dating experience.

01:19:06.700 --> 01:19:07.659
Really?

01:19:08.618 --> 01:19:09.745
What's your type?

01:19:09.828 --> 01:19:12.330
What type of guy do you like?

01:19:13.790 --> 01:19:15.459
Well, you know.

01:19:16.042 --> 01:19:17.753
Someone I feel comfortable around,
I guess.

01:19:18.628 --> 01:19:20.714
Then you probably don't like bad boys.

01:19:20.797 --> 01:19:23.425
- Jun-hui, you're out.
- You're out. Go home.

01:19:24.384 --> 01:19:26.636
Jun-hui, are you the bad boy type?

01:19:27.888 --> 01:19:29.264
No, they're just joking.

01:19:29.347 --> 01:19:31.057
Joking, my ass.

01:19:31.141 --> 01:19:33.268
Fine, let's say that is not the case.

01:19:33.602 --> 01:19:35.437
Has any girl you've hit on said no to you?

01:19:35.812 --> 01:19:37.981
No, right? That means

01:19:38.648 --> 01:19:42.444
you can seduce any girl you like--

01:19:42.527 --> 01:19:43.612
Shut your mouth.

01:19:43.695 --> 01:19:46.198
That means your success rate
is 100 percent.

01:19:49.201 --> 01:19:51.369
No, I'd say it's about 99 percent.

01:19:52.704 --> 01:19:54.915
What? What does that one percent mean?

01:19:55.582 --> 01:19:58.877
It must mean that there's one woman
whom he hasn't been able to win over.

01:19:59.461 --> 01:20:00.462
Who is it?

01:20:01.463 --> 01:20:02.672
Who's that woman?

01:20:06.301 --> 01:20:07.344
What?

01:20:13.183 --> 01:20:14.684
Just drink. Drink up.

01:20:36.498 --> 01:20:39.626
That woman Jun-hui was talking about...
Do you know who she is?

01:20:41.253 --> 01:20:42.796
How would I know?

01:20:45.715 --> 01:20:48.385
It must be someone
who's younger than us, right?

01:20:49.511 --> 01:20:51.930
We're still young too.

01:20:53.557 --> 01:20:55.725
Didn't you go on about
how you struggle to wake up

01:20:55.809 --> 01:20:57.435
because you're old now?

01:20:57.769 --> 01:21:00.939
That was just because I was too tired.

01:21:03.650 --> 01:21:05.277
I wonder what kind of girl she is.

01:21:05.360 --> 01:21:07.279
How can she not fall for his charms?

01:21:11.741 --> 01:21:14.870
By the way, why do you keep
smiling like that?

01:21:16.288 --> 01:21:17.205
Me?

01:21:17.789 --> 01:21:18.832
I didn't.

01:21:21.501 --> 01:21:23.503
He's definitely seeing someone.

01:21:25.255 --> 01:21:27.507
But they didn't go all the way yet.

01:21:29.926 --> 01:21:32.596
This is the perfect chance to make a move.

01:21:36.558 --> 01:21:38.560
I have to get on with it.

01:21:39.519 --> 01:21:40.770
I need to be bolder.

01:21:49.237 --> 01:21:50.947
But what's getting in your way?

01:21:51.114 --> 01:21:53.491
There must be a reason why

01:21:53.575 --> 01:21:55.368
a player like you is
hesitant to make a move.

01:21:56.828 --> 01:21:59.581
I'm just being cautious.

01:21:59.831 --> 01:22:02.500
What? Does that mean you're not sure
about your feelings?

01:22:03.376 --> 01:22:04.377
Not exactly.

01:22:04.961 --> 01:22:06.379
I'm sure about my feelings.

01:22:07.339 --> 01:22:09.799
- But...
- The girl isn't?

01:22:12.802 --> 01:22:15.430
I haven't asked her yet.

01:22:17.223 --> 01:22:18.975
You get nervous too?

01:22:19.893 --> 01:22:22.145
Why? Are you afraid of being rejected?

01:22:22.729 --> 01:22:24.522
That's why I said I was being cautious.

01:22:26.316 --> 01:22:28.693
Does she know that you're being so lame?

01:22:29.361 --> 01:22:31.988
Lame? What are you talking about?

01:22:32.072 --> 01:22:33.823
- Look at you.
- Wait.

01:22:34.866 --> 01:22:38.453
You must be really into her.
He seems so desperate.

01:22:38.995 --> 01:22:40.413
Stop it.

01:22:41.373 --> 01:22:43.583
Let's talk about something else.

01:22:44.042 --> 01:22:45.043
Anyhow,

01:22:45.794 --> 01:22:48.004
that means nothing is for certain yet.

01:22:49.547 --> 01:22:50.465
Aren't I right?

01:22:57.722 --> 01:22:59.099
Well,

01:22:59.182 --> 01:23:01.309
not just yet...

01:23:37.887 --> 01:23:40.890
You have no idea how important
timing is in a relationship.

01:23:40.974 --> 01:23:42.892
Are we in a relationship now?

01:23:43.727 --> 01:23:45.854
- I said you look pretty!
- Are you crazy?

01:23:45.937 --> 01:23:47.647
I am crazy for someone.

01:23:48.857 --> 01:23:51.192
Do you want to come over?

01:23:51.943 --> 01:23:54.571
Do you think it'll be okay?

01:23:55.071 --> 01:23:56.239
We are not committing a crime.

01:23:56.823 --> 01:23:58.408
You should always watch your behavior.

01:23:58.616 --> 01:23:59.492
Otherwise,

01:23:59.576 --> 01:24:01.119
- you'll be the talk of the town.
- Jin-a!

01:24:01.995 --> 01:24:04.789
Jin-a said she'd come,
but I can't reach her.

01:24:04.873 --> 01:24:06.750
- You never say no to these things.
- My gosh!

01:24:06.833 --> 01:24:07.792
What if...

01:24:08.793 --> 01:24:10.795
I regret holding your hand that day

01:24:11.379 --> 01:24:13.173
sometime in the future?

01:24:15.425 --> 01:24:17.343
I'll never leave you alone from now on.

01:24:22.140 --> 01:24:24.142
Subtitle translation by Kim Su-hyeon
